to put the knight on f5 rather than to capture on g6.} fxg6 18. Be3 {
Strategically, White doesn't want to exchange the dark-squared bishops, but in
this case with fxg6 and after} Bxe3 19. Qxe3 {Black has some weaknesses
created by b5 and White has many ideas such as Qc5, Bb3+, and also a2-a4.})
17... Rb8 18. b4 Bb6 19. Rd1 Qe7 20. axb5 axb5 21. Bd3 Rfd8 22. Be3 Bxe3 23.
