-24,203,307,1205,613,1369,1369,29983,326,326,326,431,104,205,123,103,81,195,
180,585,627,643,654]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 f5 5. d4 exd4 6. e5
b5 (6... Nge7 7. c3 {The simplest continuation, sacrificing a pawn for a
bigger lead in development.} (7. O-O $5) (7. Nxd4 {An interesting move, with
the point that} Nxe5 {runs into} 8. Ne6 {winning the queen.}) 7... dxc3 8. Nxc3
$18) 7. Bb3 Na5 8. Bd5 c6 (8... Bb7 $2 9. Bxb7 Nxb7 10. Nxd4 $18) 9. Bxg8 Rxg8
10. O-O c5 11. c3 Bb7 12. cxd4 Qe7 13. d5 {This move looks very good and it's
a nice sight with the central pawns, but it's actually an inaccuracy that
allows Black some counterplay.} (13. dxc5 $16) 13... h6 (13... g5 {This is the
move that can give Black some counterplay in the position.}) 14. Re1 Nc4 15. e6
O-O-O 16. a4 dxe6 17. axb5 axb5 18. Qe2 Bxd5 19. Nc3 Bc6 20. Ne5 Nxe5 21. Qxe5
Qd6 22. Qe2 c4 23. Bf4 Qxf4 24. Qxe6+ Kb7 25. Ra7+ Kxa7 26. Qxc6 Kb8 27. Nxb5
Bc5 28. Qxc5 Rd7 29. g3 Qf3 30. Nd6 Qb3 31. Qc6 Rgd8 32. Ra1 Ra7 33. Rxa7 Kxa7
34. Nb5+ 1-0

