1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. O-O Bd7 6. c3 g6 7. d4 Bg7 8. Re1
Nge7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Nbd2 (10. dxe5 $5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxa4 (11... Bxe5 12. Bxd7
Qxd7 13. Nd2 $14) 12. Qxa4 dxe5 13. Nd2 $14) 10... h6 (10... f5 11. exf5 gxf5
12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Nf1 $16) 11. dxe5 $1 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 $1 dxe5 13. Bxd7 (13. Qc2
$14 b5 14. Bb3 $16) 13... Qxd7 14. Nb3 $1 Qc8 (14... Qxd1 15. Rexd1 $1 (15.
Raxd1 $5) 15... b6 16. a4 (16. Rd7 {This wins of course but I would like to
illustrate a few ideas for White.}) 16... a5 17. Nd2 (17. Rd7 $18) 17... Rfd8
18. Nc4 Kf8 19. g4 {This is an interesting idea, White is placing the pawn on
the light squares, first stabilizing the knight on c4 and now taking space on
the kingside.} (19. f3 Ke8 20. Kf1 Rxd1+ 21. Rxd1 Rd8 22. Rxd8+ Kxd8 23. b4 {
A good idea with the intention of creating a passed pawn on the queenside.}))
15. Qe2 $1 b6 16. Qc4 $1 Qb7 17. Red1 $1 Rfd8 18. f3 $1 a5 19. a4 $1 Qc6 20.
Qxc6 (20. Nd2 $4 Rxd2 21. Qxc6 Rxd1+ $19) 20... Nxc6 21. Kf1 $1 Kf8 22. Ke2 Ke8
23. Nd2 $1 (23. g4 $5) 23... Bf8 24. Nc4 Rxd1 25. Rxd1 Rd8 26. Rd5 $1 (26. Rg1
$5) (26. Rb1 $5) 26... f6 27. f4 $1 exf4 28. Bxf4 Rd7 29. g4 $1 (29. h3 h5 {
Intending to exchange on g4 if White plays g2-g4.}) 29... Ne7 30. Rd3 Rxd3 31.
Kxd3 Kd7 32. Ne3 $1 Bg7 33. b4 h5 (33... axb4 34. cxb4 $16 {White will create
a distant passed pawn on the queenside.}) 34. gxh5 gxh5 35. Kc4 Ng6 36. Nd5 $1
Ne5+ 37. Bxe5 fxe5 38. Ne3 axb4 39. cxb4 c6 40. Nf5 Bf8 41. h3 $1 Ke6 42. b5 $1
(42. a5 b5+ 43. Kb3 $18) 42... c5 (42... Kd7 43. Ng3 h4 44. Nf5 $18) 43. h4 $1
Bd6 (43... Be7 44. Nxe7 Kxe7 45. Kd5 Kd7 46. Kxe5 Ke7 47. Kd5 Kd7 48. e5 Ke7
49. e6 c4 (49... Kd8 50. a5 bxa5 51. b6 $18) 50. Kxc4 Kxe6 51. Kb4 $1 (51. Kb3
Kd6 52. Kb4 Kc7 53. Kc4 $18 (53. a5 $4 bxa5+ 54. Kxa5 Kb7 $11) 53... Kd6 54.
Kd4 Ke6 55. Ke4 Kf6 (55... Kd6 56. Kf5 $18) 56. a5 $18 (56. Kd5 $18)) 51... Kd6
52. a5 $18) 44. Ng7+ Kd7 45. Nxh5 Be7 46. Kd5 Bxh4 47. Kxe5 c4 48. Kd4 c3 49.
Kxc3 Kd6 50. Kd3 Kc5 51. Nf4 1-0

