1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O (5. d3 {Is our move order.})
5... b5 6. Bb3 Bb7 7. d3 Be7 8. c4 bxc4 9. Bxc4 O-O 10. Nc3 d6 {Threatening
Na5.} 11. a3 Nd4 12. b4 (12. Nxd4 exd4 13. Nd5 c5 {Black is threatening to
capture on d5 now since the c-pawn won't be weak anymore, however, it is White
to move.} (13... Nxd5 14. exd5 a5 15. Bd2 Bf6 (15... a4 {Fixing White's pawns
like this doesn't mean anything as now it may be even easier to create a
passed a-pawn for White.} 16. b3 axb3 17. Qxb3 $16) 16. b4 $14) 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7
15. Bg5 $16 {The pin is quite annoying but if Black gets rid of it with} h6 16.
Bh4 g5 17. Bg3 {Black has weakened the kingside a lot.}) 12... Nxf3+ 13. Qxf3
c6 14. Bg5 h6 15. Bh4 Bc8 16. h3 Be6 17. Rfd1 Qb6 18. Rac1 Rfd8 19. Na4 Qb7 20.
Bxe6 fxe6 21. d4 exd4 22. Rxd4 a5 23. Qb3 Kf7 24. Rdc4 axb4 25. Rxb4 Qa6 26.
Bxf6 Bxf6 27. Nb6 Qxa3 28. Qc4 d5 29. exd5 cxd5 30. Qc7+ Kg8 31. Rcb1 Ra7 32.
