1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O b5 6. Bb3 Bb7 7. d3 Be7 8. c4
O-O 9. Nc3 bxc4 10. Bxc4 d6 11. Be3 (11. a3 $1 {This is a better choice in my
opinion.} h6 (11... Nb8 12. Be3 Nbd7 13. b4 {With a pleasant position.} (13.
Qc2 $5) (13. Ng5 $5 {This is an interesting idea to consider but only if Black
can't defend easily, with the point to capture on f7 and play Qb3 and to pick
up the bishop on b7.})) 12. Be3 Ng4 {White also could have played 12.h3 but
this isn't a big threat because after} (12... Nd7 {In this line for example,
now h3 isn't needed, so that's why Be3 and not h3.} 13. Rc1 $16 (13. Nd5 $5) (
13. d4 $5)) 13. Bd2 {the knight is misplaced on g4, so White can play h3 later
on if White wants to.}) 11... Na5 12. Bd5 (12. Nd2 $5 {This seems like a
continuation to consider with the point that if Black captures on c4, to
recapture with the pawn.}) 12... c6 13. Bxf7+ Rxf7 14. b4 {This is a typical
idea but here it's not very impressive.} Bc8 15. bxa5 Bg4 {Black has a nice
compensation for the pawn.} 16. Kh1 Nh5 17. Qb3 Bxf3 18. gxf3 Qd7 19. Ne2 Raf8
20. Rab1 Bd8 21. Ng1 Bxa5 22. Qa4 Bc3 23. Rfc1 Bd4 24. Qxc6 Qa7 25. Re1 Qe7 26.
Qxa6 Nf4 27. Rec1 Qg5 28. Bxf4 Qxf4 29. Rc8 h6 30. Rbb8 Rxc8 31. Qxc8+ Kh7 32.
Qg8+ Kg6 33. Qe8 Kh7 34. Qg8+ Kg6 35. Rd8 Bxf2 36. Rxd6+ Kh5 37. Qc8 Qg5 38.
Nh3 Qc1+ 1-0

