{In this section we are going to see the structure, arising after the
following typical moves.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. O-O Nd4
6. Be3 Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3 Bxe3 8. Qxe3 c6 9. Bc4 O-O 10. Bb3 Re8 11. f4 d6 12. fxe5
dxe5 13. Nd2 {White's plans are a4-h3-Kh1 and slowly improve our pieces. We
can try to create small threats on the kingside like Qg3-Nc4-Ne3-Nf5 or
sometimes also try to push pawns on the queenside after the queens have been
traded.} *

