{In this section, we are going to see structures with semi open files,
typically when fe5 is met by a capture by a piece or Black captures on f4. You
will understand what I mean, in a moment.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3
Bc5 5. O-O Nd4 6. Be3 Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3 Bxe3 8. Qxe3 c6 9. Bc4 O-O 10. Bb3 d6 11.
Nd2 Qe7 12. f4 Be6 13. Rae1 exf4 14. Rxf4 {White has good control of the
f-file and he can eventually expand on the queenside with moves like a4-a5,
Ra1, etc. It was probably better to not play Rae1 for the same reason.} *

