{In this section we are going to see model games for the slow Italian
structures.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 $1 {After this move. A big
fight in the middlegame is about to take place!} Bc5 {By far the most common
move, however there are some playable alternatives.} 5. O-O Nd4 {by far the
most common move and the reason why 5.0-0 is not the most common move, but an
unpleasant surprise is waiting for Black!} 6. Be3 $1 {A very intresting and
rare line, after this move we manage to get a small advantage (or a big one! )
in a position with several possibilities! That's the best deal for white
against the Berlin Spanish.} Nxf3+ {this should be the best.} 7. Qxf3 Bxe3 8.
Qxe3 $1 {Our queen stands perfectly on e3, controlling many important squares.}
c6 9. Bc4 $1 O-O 10. Bb3 $1 {This is the basic position of the Berlin with
d3-Be3! It's a big battlefield with many possible ideas for both sides and a
very interesting play for White. Our main idea is Bb3-Nd2 and f4! intending
fe5! and whenever Black goes a5...we go a4!} d6 11. Nd2 a5 12. a4 Be6 13. Bxe6
fxe6 14. c3 $14 Qe7 15. Nc4 {White has a good version of the Italian. Note:
This section also contains other types of structures which don't fit or come
from Italian.} *

