1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 (5... b5 6. Bb3 Be7 7. O-O
O-O 8. Re1 d6 9. a3 {While, we can also play c3 this one might actually turn
out to be better.} Na5 10. Ba2 c5 11. Nbd2 {followed by Nf1-Ne3.}) 6. c3 g6 7.
O-O Bg7 8. Re1 O-O 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bh4 Qe8 11. Nbd2 Nd7 (11... Nh5 12. Bxc6 {
slightly counterintutive but works well.} bxc6 13. d4 {White is slightly
better.}) 12. Nf1 Nc5 (12... f5 13. exf5 gxf5 14. d4 e4 {is something which we
usually want to avoid.}) 13. Bc2 Ne6 14. Ne3 Ne7 15. d4 {stopping f5 for now.}
Nf4 16. Bg3 b5 17. a4 Bd7 18. axb5 Bxb5 (18... axb5 19. Rxa8 Qxa8 20. dxe5 {
wins material.}) 19. c4 Bc6 20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. exd5 Nh5 22. dxe5 Nxg3 23. hxg3
dxe5 24. Nxe5 Qd8 25. b4 Qd6 26. c5 Qxd5 27. Nxg6 fxg6 28. Bb3 1-0

