1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. c3 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. Re1
O-O 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bh4 Bd7 11. Nbd2 Qe8 {This plan is quite typical as we have
seen before to create threats like Nd4.} 12. Nf1 (12. d4 Nxd4 {exactly Black's
aim.}) 12... Nh5 13. Ne3 Nf4 (13... f5 14. exf5 gxf5 15. Nd5 {White wins
material.}) 14. Bb3 Kh8 15. d4 f6 (15... f5 {You can't just try for a flank
attack with an open center. It fails miserably.} 16. exf5 gxf5 17. dxe5 dxe5
18. Bg3 Ng6 19. Nd5 {Black has too many targets.}) 16. Bg3 Nh5 (16... Rc8 17.
Bxf4 exf4 18. Nd5 g5 19. Qd3 {Black's light squares might become target at any
moment.}) 17. Nd5 Rc8 18. Nh4 Kh7 19. f4 exf4 20. Nxf4 Nxf4 21. Bxf4 Ne7 22.
Bg3 Qd8 23. Qf3 b5 24. Bc2 f5 25. exf5 Nxf5 26. Nxf5 Bxf5 27. Bxf5 Rxf5 28. Qc6
