{[%evp 0,65,28,11,13,22,22,22,34,2,2,2,9,-27,2,2,2,0,0,0,5,0,15,15,16,11,41,39,
49,41,31,33,115,70,61,82,107,82,72,72,96,31,61,78,97,90,109,98,149,167,186,212,
305,365,401,414,412,276,446,444,444,465,465,413,434,414,570,656] An
interesting game of mine, in the typical lines of the d3 Spanish!} 1. e4 e5 2.
Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 (5. O-O Be7 6. d3 {Transposes but Black
could have taken on e4 leading to Open Spainsh.}) 5... d6 6. c3 g6 7. O-O Bg7
8. Re1 O-O 9. h3 {Our idea behind h3 is definetly d4.} b5 10. Bc2 (10. Bb3 {
It doesn't make much sense to give Na5-c5 as tempo.} Na5 11. Bc2 c5 12. Nbd2
Re8 13. d4 exd4 14. cxd4 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Bb7 {Black is good.}) 10... Bb7 11. Be3
Re8 12. Nbd2 Nb8 (12... d5 13. Bg5 dxe4 14. Nxe4 {My favourite way to
recapture.}) 13. b4 Nbd7 14. a4 (14. Nb3 Rb8 15. Na5 Ba8 {is also possible and
next we can go with a4.}) 14... c5 15. Qb1 Rb8 16. axb5 axb5 17. Ra5 Ba8 18.
Qa2 cxb4 19. cxb4 Bf8 20. Nb3 $2 (20. Bb3 $18 {This is the most natural move
but, I didn't calculate it during the game.} d5 21. exd5 Bxb4 22. Ra7 Bc5 23.
d6 $3 Bxa7 24. Bxf7+ Kg7 25. Bxa7 Bxf3 26. Nxf3 Ra8 27. Bxe8 Qxe8 28. Rc1 $18 {
White is clearly better.}) (20. Ra7 {Even this is better then text.}) 20... d5
21. Nc5 Rc8 $2 (21... Nxc5 {This is highly complex, but Black can save by
concrete play.} 22. Bxc5 Bxc5 23. bxc5 Qc8 24. Ra6 Nd7 25. exd5 Nxc5 26. Ra7 b4
$13 {And this has no end.}) 22. Rxb5 $18 {White should now get an easy win.} d4
23. Bd2 Nxc5 24. bxc5 h6 25. Bb3 Qd7 26. c6 Qc7 27. Ba5 Qa7 28. Nxe5 Bxc6 29.
Bxf7+ Kg7 30. Bxe8 Bxe8 31. Rb2 Ra8 32. Qe6 $1 Ba4 33. Reb1 1-0

