{In this section we are going to see model games arising in the following
setup.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 Bc5 6. c3 b5 7. Bb3 $1
d6 8. Bg5 h6 9. Bh4 Bd7 10. O-O Bb6 11. a4 $1 {Incredible idea to create play
on queenside.} Rb8 12. axb5 axb5 13. Na3 $3 $14 {This idea is quite rare in
other lines, but here it works really well. If Black plays b4, it weakens his
c4 square and if he moves the Bishop there are always tactics connected on the
a-file.} *

