1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 Bc5 (5... b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. Nc3 {
This used to be a good option, however nowadays it doesn't have a good
reputation.} d6 8. Nd5 h6 9. c3 Rb8 {And Black can simply delay castling.} (
9... O-O 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6 11. Bd5 Bd7 12. Rg1 {This is trick! White is planning
g4-g5 with good attacking chances.})) (5... Be7 6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. Nxe5 {simply
wins a pawn.}) 6. c3 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. Bg5 h6 9. Bh4 g5 10. Bg3 Qe7 11. a4 Rb8
12. axb5 axb5 13. O-O Bd7 14. Re1 $16 O-O 15. d4 Bb6 16. Na3 Bg4 17. Nxb5 $1 (
17. Bd5 $3 $16 {This is actually better.}) 17... Bxf3 18. Qxf3 exd4 19. Qf5 $3
Kg7 20. Bd5 $3 Ne5 21. Nxd4 $16 1-0

