1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. c3 d6 8. Bg5 h6
9. Bh4 O-O 10. O-O Bb6 11. a4 $1 Rb8 12. axb5 axb5 13. Na3 $1 b4 $2 (13... Na5
$1 14. Ba2 $14 {Once, we have opened the a-file, we can manuever our pieces
for good.} c6 15. b4 Nb7 16. Nc2 g5 17. Bg3 Qe7 18. Ne3 Bxe3 19. fxe3 Nd8 20.
Nh4 $3 $16 {Brilliant and wins.}) (13... Bd7 14. Nxb5 $1 Bxf2+ $2 15. Rxf2 Rxb5
16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Nd4 $18 {We have seen this trick before.}) 14. Nc4 $16 bxc3
15. bxc3 Be6 16. Ba2 $1 (16. Nxb6 Bxb3 17. Qxb3 Rxb6 18. Qd1 $3 {The play is
on the kingside.} g5 (18... Qe7 19. Re1) 19. Nxg5 hxg5 20. Bxg5 {followed by
f4.}) 16... g5 17. Nxg5 $3 (17. Bg3 $6 Ra8 {too passive, Black is in the game
now!}) 17... hxg5 18. Bxg5 Bxc4 19. Bxc4 Kg7 20. Kh1 Qd7 21. f4 $18 Ng4 22. f5
Nf6 23. Rf3 Rh8 24. Rg3 Nh5 25. f6+ Kf8 26. Rh3 Qxh3 27. gxh3 Nf4 28. Bxf4 exf4
29. Qg4 Rg8 30. Qd7 f3 31. Qxf7# 1-0

