1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. c3 d6 8. Bg5 h6
9. Bh4 g5 (9... Bd7 10. O-O O-O 11. d4 $1 Bb6 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Bxf6 {We have
seen this trick multiple times by now.}) 10. Bg3 O-O 11. Nbd2 Kg7 12. Nf1 $5 (
12. O-O $1 {is much better. We play a similar version of slow italian but with
the Bishop on g3 and good central control.} Be6 (12... Nh7 $4 {you can't leave
the center like this.} 13. Bd5 Bd7 14. d4 $18 {wins on the spot.}) (12... a5 $2
13. a4 b4 14. Nc4 $16 {followed by Ne3-Nf5 at some point.}) (12... Bd7 13. Re1
$1 {White is planning Nf1-Ne3 and d4.} Nh5 (13... Re8 14. Nf1 $16 Bb6 15. Ne3
Bxe3 16. Rxe3 $1 {After this Bishop has been traded, there is no attack left
for Black. While, White will play on Black's weaknesses.}) 14. Nxe5 $3 $18 {
winning material.}) 13. Re1 $1 Bxb3 14. Nxb3 $1 Bb6 15. d4 Re8 16. Qc2 $16 {
White has good central control.}) 12... Ne7 13. Ne3 Ng6 14. Qc2 Ng4 15. Nf1 f5
16. exf5 Bxf5 17. h3 Bxd3 18. Qxd3 Nxf2 19. Bxf2 Nf4 20. Qe4 Nxg2+ 21. Kd1 Bxf2
22. Bc2 Rf6 23. Rh2 Qg8 24. Rxg2 d5 25. Qg4 Raf8 26. Nxg5 Kh8 27. Nh7 Qxg4+ 28.
hxg4 1-0

